        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 26 at 6:17PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 616 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northeast of Zortman, moving southeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Malta, Dodson, Phillips, and Wagner.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM MDT for
northeastern Montana.</instruction>
